<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.167927>
    dc:description "FIGURES 13 – 18. Ceriana adults, overall appearance, dorsal view. 13 Ceriana conopsoides male, Greece 14 Ceriana conopsoides male, Estonia 15 Ceriana conopsoides female, Russia 16 Ceriana media sp. n. male, paratype, Afghanistan 17 Ceriana skevingtoni sp. n. male, paratype, Azerbaijan 18 Ceriana skevingtoni sp. n. female, paratype, Azerbaijan. Scale line = 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/167927/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.167930>
    dc:description "FIGURES 31 – 36. Ceriana adults, overall appearance, lateral view. 31 Ceriana conopsoides male, Greece 32 Ceriana conopsoides female, Russia 33 Ceriana media sp. n. male, paratype, Afghanistan 34 Ceriana media sp. n. female, paratype, Iran 35 Ceriana skevingtoni sp. n. male, paratype, Azerbaijan 36 Ceriana skevingtoni sp. n. female, paratype, Azerbaijan Talish. Scale line = 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/167930/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.167931>
    dc:description "FIGURES 37 – 48. Head, frontal view. 37 Ceriana brunettii male, Tajikistan 38 Ceriana caesarea male, Turkmenistan 39 Ceriana conopsoides male, Greece 40 Ceriana conopsoides female, Russia 41 Ceriana glaebosa male paratype 42 Ceriana media male paratype, Afghanistan 43 Ceriana naja male, Tajikistan 44 Ceriana sartorum male, Turkmenistan 45 Ceriana sartorum female, Tajikistan 46 Ceriana skevingtoni male paratype, Azerbaijan Talish 47 Ceriana vespiformis male, Greece 48 Ceriana vespiformis female, Rhodos. Scale line = 2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/167931/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.167938>
    dc:description "FIGURES 83 – 86. Mesofemur of Ceriana species, male, ventro-lateral view. 83 Ceriana caesarea, Turkmenistan 84 Ceriana conopsoides, Russia 85 Ceriana media sp. n., paratype 86 Ceriana skevingtoni sp. n., holotype. Scale line = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/167938/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.167942>
    dc:description "FIGURES 98 – 101. Metafemur of Ceriana species 98 Ceriana conopsoides male, Russia 99 Ceriana conopsoides female, Sweden 100 Ceriana media sp. n., holotype 101 Ceriana skevingtoni sp. n. paratype, male. Scale line = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/167942/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.167944>
    dc:description "FIGURES 106 – 108. Male genitalia of Ceriana skevingtoni sp. n., paratype 106 Epandrium and hypandrium, lateral view 107 Epandrium, dorsal view 108 Hypandrium, ventral view. Scale line = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/167944/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.167957>
    dc:description "FIGURES 166 – 168. Distribution maps of the West-Palaearctic Cerioidini. 166 Ceriana brunettii (yellow circle), Ceriana caesarea (blue square) and Ceriana media (red triangle) 167 Ceriana naja (blue circle), Ceriana sartorum (yellow triangle) and Ceriana skevingtoni (red square) 168 Ceriana conopsoides (purple circle)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/167957/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

